hey can&#39;t get anything for the money]."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1195.605","u": "[Whispers] Well, I don&#39;t know that either."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1198.199","u": "Now well. Do the peasants barter for cigarettes?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1201.643","u": "Surely they, too, because they are heavy smokers."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1205.233","u": "And they give quite a bit for them?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1207.787","u": "They give a lot for them. I heard that someone paid 90 marks for a package of cigarettes [the official exchange, as far as I remember, was about 10 marks to the dollar, or less]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1213.940","u": "90 marks?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1214.568","u": "30 [?] marks."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1215.378","u": "Nu, yes. One pays in France about 150 to 175 franks [official exchange of 117 franks to the dollar]."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1221.304","u": "Hm. Well, that is something that most people would be unable to understand."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1225.491","u": "Hm. Now tell me something else. How do you explain that most of the Germans are so well dressed?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1235.611","u": "Hm. Many still had reserves, those who have preserved their homes, but most of the people are really not so well dressed any more. Most of the people were bombed out and had lost everything."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1250.306","u": "Now what has become of all the clothing which was taken from the Jews, let us say in Theresienstadt, and was taken away everywhere before they were transported? [See Mr. Schlaefrig, Chapter 26.]"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1259.722","u": "Well, you must consider that the warehouses [?] were bombed out, that all the things went up in flames."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1268.142","u": "So that you think . . ."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1268.598","u": "So everything is gone. Take for instance, Dresden."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1271.935","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1272.085","u": "Dresden is completely destroyed, and with it all the clothing and everything. We, for instance, got out of our home only with that which I had on my body. Everything else was gone."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1283.240","u": "Oh, you were bombed out in Dresden?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1284.824","u": "Completely bombed out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1286.674","u": "When did that happen?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1287.621","u": "On the 13th of February, &#39;45."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1290.055","u": "What was there, an air attack? By whom?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1293.999","u": "I don&#39;t know. It was at night."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1295.726","u": "At night?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1296.261","u": "And whooo!"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1298.439","u": "And there was a big bombardment."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1300.940","u": "There was a big bombardment."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1301.289","u": "And where did you and your family go for safety?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1305.436","u": "We were in a common shelter at the railroad station."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1308.624","u": "Ah."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1308.987","u": "Dresden had not a single bunker. It was completely without protection."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1313.812","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1314.108","u": "Only the governer had a large bunker for his family."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1317.020","u": "How come that here they had not dug bunkers?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1320.354","u": "Well, that depended on . . . on the Gauleiter [governor appointed by the central government]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1324.887","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1325.365","u": "On him [?]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1325.823","u": "Now then. You went to the railroad station. But that was the most dangerous place?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1331.229","u": "Well, yes. We were first in our cellar, at the first attack."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1334.256","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1334.902","u": "But then our house was not damaged. There fell only incendiaries in the neighborhood."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1340.595","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1340.862","u": "Then we went to the suburb to see our old parents."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1344.762","u": "Your parents or those of your husband?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1346.256","u": "My husband&#39;s parents. My father-in-law had died then at the age of 84 after the attack."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1351.853","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1352.188","u": "My mother-in-law is still alive at the age of 78."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1355.371","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1356.175","u": "Also my father [is still alive]. And when we went to the station [?] to get home there was a second alarm."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1364.600","u": "[Words not clear.]"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1365.521","u": "There was no more time [words not clear]. So we had to take refuge in the railroad station, in the railroad station&#39;s shelter."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1371.788","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1372.772","u": "And . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1373.612","u": "Was the railroad station&#39;s shelter underground?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1375.728","u": "Underground."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1376.532","u": "Those must have been the tunnels [for pedestrians] which are [located] underground."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1378.648","u": "No, no. These were the shelters of the administration of the government bank."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1382.942","u": "Ja."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1383.241","u": "In a large all-brick house."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1385.871","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1386.317","u": "Very large. There stood [word not clear]. To be sure, hundreds of people have perished. And by a miracle we got out, that is my son, my little one, and I. We climbed out after all clear [?] through a break [in the floor?] . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1401.625","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1401.951","u": "And . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1403.174","u": "Your husband?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1403.541","u": "My husband returned only the next morning at eight."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1405.971","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1406.465","u": "So all day we thought my husband was dead, and he thought that we were dead."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1410.783","u": "You didn&#39;t . . . he did not know that you got out."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1413.105","u": "No. We met only the next evening."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1416.010","u": "At home."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1416.838","u": "No. In the meantime our house, too, was gone."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1419.169","u": "Oh, the house was gone."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1420.212","u": "Completely demolished."},    {"wh