475.061","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1475.318","u": "Then to Sweden."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1476.211","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1476.320","u": "Then to America."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1477.413","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1478.119","u": "And on the day of his death . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1480.035","u": "Again in Thuringia."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1480.541","u": ". . . landed again in Thuringia [incorrect: Cologne is not in Thuringia, but is in the Rhine province] in order to die there."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1485.385","u": "And your mother-in-law?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1486.739","u": "My mother-in-law still lived in Coburg."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1488.906","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1490.953","u": "We took her then to Coburg so that she could remain in the American Zone."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1495.997","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1496.308","u": "You see [?]? so that she would be in contact with us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1498.391","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1498.714","u": "And Dresden belongs to the Russian Zone."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1500.717","u": "And who supports her?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1502.409","u": "For the time being she has enough to live on, and we hope [chuckle] that we will be able from there to send here somthing to eat. Maybe . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1509.132","u": "Aha. Did your acquaintances from America send you anything during this time [after the armistace]?"},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1513.730","u": "No. We received letters, but since everybody hoped that we shall soon return, they thought it not worthwhile [hearty laughter], and that is why . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1522.769","u": "[Cordially] Well, now, you will soon be in America."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1525.218","u": "We hope . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1525.763","u": "[In English] This concludes the interview with Mrs. Charlotte Schultze, wife of a physician, hm, what they call here a German Aryan, who is now in the United States with the child, and will probably send over the affidavit for the wife . . . for his wife. We conclude the interview at 8 minutes of the counter index. An Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording. Munich, Germany. September the 20th, 1946."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1556.859","u": "[In German] Thank you very much, Frau doctor."},    {"who": "Charlotte Schultze", "start": "1559.146","u": "There you are then . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1565.326","u": "[In English] This concludes Spool 137A. The other part will be Spool 137B and is the beginning of Bassfreund&#39;s story. It may be advisable since we have only 8 minutes on this spool to combine this one with 136B and have Mrs. Charlotte Schultze all on one spool. But we will leave that for further checkup. Boder. October the 13th, 1950. MH156."}        ]
